    <note type="biography">
        <p>Scottish shoemaker and naturalist. Shoemaker in Banff until 1875. Collected, mounted, and exhibited local zoological specimens. Curator of a museum in Banff. Opened an unsuccessful museum of natural history in Aberdeen. Contributed to the <hi rend="italic">Zoologist.</hi> Elected an associate of the Linnean Society of London, 1866.</p></note>
